  2. Middle layer: Blue block
  3. Left side: Green block
  4. Top: Yellow block on both sides/edges

Block Dictionary Selection:
- Block 3 (Red cube) for bottom layer
- Block 1 (Blue cube) for middle layer
- Block 2 (Green cube) for side block
- Block 4 (Yellow cube) and Block 12 (Yellow rectangular block) for top/edges

Assembly Instructions:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 3 (Red)
    Step2: Move block with index 1 (Blue) on top of Red
    Step3: Move block with index 2 (Green) to the side
    Step4: Move block with index 4 (Yellow cube) on one side
    Step5: Move block with index 12 (Yellow rectangular block) on the other side
}

The assembly follows the spatial arrangement shown in the target structure, using blocks exactly as they appear in the dictionary.
